cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about unsupervised information retrieval using neural vector space models. The most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper focuses on improving document ranking. The paper also uses natural language processing techniques, which suggests it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of gradient descent and neural networks suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for learning document representations, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
